 that the proponents of same-sex marriage will eventually be successful , just as human rights advocates were with slavery , voting , and interracial marriage .


root(ROOT-0, successful-10)
mark(successful-10, that-1)
det(proponents-3, the-2)
nsubj(successful-10, proponents-3)
amod(marriage-6, same-sex-5)
prep_of(proponents-3, marriage-6)
aux(successful-10, will-7)
advmod(successful-10, eventually-8)
cop(successful-10, be-9)
advmod(were-17, just-12)
mark(were-17, as-13)
amod(advocates-16, human-14)
nn(advocates-16, rights-15)
nsubj(were-17, advocates-16)
advcl(successful-10, were-17)
prep_with(were-17, slavery-19)
prep_with(were-17, voting-21)
conj_and(slavery-19, voting-21)
amod(marriage-25, interracial-24)
prep_with(were-17, marriage-25)
conj_and(slavery-19, marriage-25)

He states that by not allowing gay marriage, if a divorce occurs the state would have to care for the dependent partner, instead of the richer partner as in heterosexual marriages.
root(ROOT-0, states-2)
